OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F397A1753122702
OL,3,CMore than 200 pupils suspended from
OL,4,Csecondary school in three weeks
OL,6,FHe added: "I have no issues with my
OL,7,Fchild being punished; however, it
OL,8,Fshould be relevant to the offence and
OL,9,Fwarranted, and I believe there should
OL,10,Fbe a process or steps taken to avoid
OL,11,Fsuspensions. Suspension should always
OL,12,Fbe a last resort once every other
OL,13,Favenue is exhausted.
OL,15,F"Right now there are mass isolations,
OL,16,Fmass suspensions and mass numbers of
OL,17,Fpupils missing valuable time in the
OL,18,Fclassroom, therefore affecting their
OL,19,Flearning."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/15
