OL,3,CMore than 200 pupils suspended from
OL,4,Csecondary school in three weeks
OL,6,FMs McKenna added: "Inevitably, there
OL,7,Fare also some students who have pushed
OL,8,Fback and are testing the new
OL,9,Fboundaries of what is expected of
OL,10,Fthem. This has led to a spike in the
OL,11,Fnumber of sanctions that have been
OL,12,Fgiven ` but, just two weeks in, we are
OL,13,Falready seeing a significant drop (of
OL,14,Fabout two-thirds) in things like short-
OL,15,Fterm exclusions. We expect this
OL,16,Ftrajectory to continue.
OL,18,F"Importantly, we are also doing more
OL,19,Fto celebrate those students who are
OL,20,Fworking hard and thriving ` it is not
OL,21,Fjust about sanctions.
OL,26,@nD@SOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/15
